> Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.

**Goal:** Refactor the stt-long-transcription codebase from a monolithic `app.py` into
a modular, free-tier-durable ASR service where the HF Dataset repo owns all durable
job state and the Space operates as a stateless execution surface with a volatile
in-memory cache for live UI rendering.

**Architecture:** The five-module inference pipeline (loader → preprocess → chunker →
decoder → postprocess) handles all audio processing. The state layer (job_store +
cache) separates durable writes to the HF Dataset repo from fast volatile reads used
by the Gradio UI. The scheduler layer (admission + queue) enforces duration-based
weighted concurrency before any audio touches the inference pipeline.

**Tech Stack:** Python 3.10+, Gradio 4.x, transformers (Wav2Vec2BertForCTC),
torchaudio, pydub, huggingface_hub, asyncio, pytest, jiwer

